profile:
The Re-Leaf Group Services: Tree Pruning, Tree and Shrub Removal, Stump Removal, Insect/Disease Control, Hedge Trimming, Deep Root Fertilizing, Tree Planting, Cable and Bracing, 24/7 Storm Emergency clean up, Aborist Reports, Firewood, Emerald Ash borer diagnosis. EAB 

___________________________________________
Andrew Evans H.L.T. is the owner and founder of ReLeaf Group and an International Society of Arboriculture (ISA) Certified Arborist.

Andrew unearthed his passion for trees during his high school summer vacation job at a local nursery, where he was introduced to all the different trees, shrubs, annuals and perennials.  His first experience with nature was a lasting one.  After two summers at the nursery he was hired as an Ontario junior ranger with the Ministry of Natural Resources and was stationed in northern Ontario, tasked with maintaining canoe portage trails and tree planting.

After graduating from high school, he knew he wanted to pursue a career in the green industry. He spent the next three years studying at Humber College graduating with honors in arboriculture (the care of trees) and received an honours diploma in landscape horticulture.  He was awarded the Board of Governors' Award, which honours the most accomplished student.

From Humber College, Andrew was immediately hired by the City of Toronto and over the next thirteen years he was involved in pruning, removal, planting, fertilizing and inspection of trees in city parks and streets.  As part of an select group, he spent six of those years working under contract to the Canadian Food Inspection Agency where he was trained to inspect trees for infestation of the Asian Long Horned Beetle and the Emerald Ash Borer.

The ReLeaf Group was founded as a part-time business to provide tree care service to private home owners but his exceptional reputation soon grew his business into a full time venture.


Extensive credentials combined with expansive experience!

_____________________________________________
    Andrew has earned the following certification and licenses:

            International Society of Arboriculture (ISA) certified Arborist ON-0300
            Member of the ISA Ontario Chapter.
            DZ drivers license
            CPR first aid.
            Arbormaster Training and Education:
            Tree climbing 1,2
            Chainsaw safety
            Technical tree felling
            Integrated risk assessment
            Technical rigging
            Emergency readiness and high angle rescue
            E.V.S.A. Electrical Utility Safety Association training course
            Ontario Ministry Training College and Universities Certified Utility Arborist
            Completed in the ISA Ontario tree climbing championships

profile:
We at Warriors Tree Removal have the expertise to tend to tree removal, pruning, crane assisted tree removal.  We're also using technology like Drones to better assist in the expert execution of the services we provide.

Traditionally Trees are remove in one of  (or a combination of) 3 differnent methods.

Felling.  This is the fastest way to get a tree on the ground.  Felling a tree is the method in which a tree is cut from the base and it falls to the ground in one piece.  This method is great for properties with enough space such as farms or large city lots.  The advantage of this method is speed.  The disadvantage is that you require enough space and that you care very little about the grass or landscaping surounding the tree, as divids usually occur.

Climbing and Rigging.  This is the slowest way to get a tree on the ground.  Climbing and Rigging is just that, a climber climbs into the tree and uses ropes, pulleys and groundsmen to dismantle a tree limb by limb.  This method is great for properties with limited landing space or obstacles in the way of the tree.  

Bucket Truck Removal.  This method is faster then climbing because the operatior is lifted into the tree he needs to work on and does not need to set ropes in the tree for safety.  Bucket Truck jobs somtimes require rigging branches away from obstacles, but for the most part brush and branches are dropped onto protective mats that are placed in the landing zone.  The disadvantage to using the Bucket Truck is our reach.  If we can reach your tree with the Bucket Truck this is the best option.

No matter what method we use to remove your Tree you can rest asured that Warriors Tree Removal uses staff that is trained and experienced in all methods of Tree Removal.

Crane Removal
Warriors Tree Removal works in partnership with Amherst Crane, together we have developed a safe and time effective method for removing trees with the use of a large crane.   

The Advantages:
Saftey for our employees and your property.  Less cutting in the air means less chance of error.  Most of the tree is cut safely at ground level in our landing zone.  With most trees we remove, they are coming down f or a reason, they are dead or dangerous.  Dead trees are dry and unpredictable, making it not safe to climb.  Using the crane method are climbers are in a much better position to stay safe.

Speed.  We can usually finish what would take us or our competitors a week to finish in about 5 hours.  Meaning you don't have worker disturbing your neighbors, your schedule or the enjoyment of your property any longer then you need to.  

Less Messy.  Lets face it, removing a tree is a messy job.  When using our crane removal service your tree is lifted from where it stands to our landing zone.  No dragging brush from your back yard to your front, no dropping fire wood onto your nice lawn, no sticks or branches in your pool.

Cost effective.  As they say "time is money" and because we have done so many crane removals we are able to get your job done fast.  Running a crane is expensive, but because we are able to work fast and schedule multiple jobs in one location, we are able to pass the savings along to our customers.

The Traditional method of pruning

We at Warriors are taking a new approah to tree pruning.  Traditionally when you call a tree service to get your tree prunned you get an estimator show up to your property to give you a quote.  This quote is based on a guess of how much time will be required to complete the job plus travel time plus the estimators time for the "free estimate".  Most estimators guess how long it will take, and add room for error, in their favor.  All this adds up to you, the customer, paying for more than you need to.  The other major problem with the traditional method is that most times the estimator and the climber are two different people leaving room for miscomunication, leading to the prune not being exactly what you wanted.

Our Solution

Rent a climber.  Renting one of our ISA trained and certified tree climber and saftey groundsmen is easier then renting a tool from a Rent-All center.  Here is how it works:  

Step 1 - Call our friendly customer service rep and schedule your prefered rental time.                                                                                                                                                             Step 2 - Be home for the arrival time of your rental.                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Step 3 - Be prepared to discuse with the climber your goals for the prune.                                                                                                                                                                                 Step 4 - Listen to the climbers suggestions on proper arborocultural practices to ensure the health of your tree is not compermised.                                                                                       Step 5 - Arrange to be home at the estimated finish time to give your "stamp of approval".

Rentals Include

* 1 climber, 1 groundsman and all their equipment.                                                                                                                                                                                                                    *Travel time and debris dump time,                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            *On site consultation with the climber                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      *Expert rigging for controlled limb removal                                                                                                                                                                                                                              *Full clean-up and debris removal                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              *Full insurance and WSIB coverage

As technology grows, so are we here at Warriors Tree Removal and the use of Drones seems to us to be the way of the future for tree care.  A drone is a radio controlled flying  camera for lack of a better definition.  Drones have the ability to send live or recorded video from the air to the operator.  

We have started using Drones on our jobsites to take fantasic birds eye views of property, trees and surounding areas.  Our hope for the future is having the ability to do tree inspections and quotes without having to leave the ground.  We are not quite at that point yet, however we are working hard to accomplish this goal.
